## 8. Implementation Phases

> Phases reorganized: **Flutter UI + Backend first** → **Unity 3D** → **Integration**

---

### PART A: Flutter UI + Backend (Weeks 1–6)

#### Phase 1: Foundation & Backend Setup (Week 1–2)

**Flutter Foundation:**
- [ ] Initialize Flutter project with `pubspec.yaml` dependencies
- [ ] Implement design system: `app_theme.dart` (Space Grotesk, dark ThemeData), `colors.dart`, `glass_card.dart`, `gradient_button.dart`, `neon_badge.dart`, `progress_ring.dart`
- [ ] Set up GoRouter with all 11 routes + persistent `BottomNavigationBar`
- [ ] Create repository pattern layer (`AuthRepository`, `TaskRepository`, `StreakRepository`, `LeaderboardRepository`, `NeighborhoodRepository`, `ShopRepository`)
- [ ] Set up Riverpod providers for all repositories

**Backend Setup:**
- [ ] Create Supabase project + configure environment variables
- [ ] Run migration `001_core_tables.sql` — create all 13 tables with triggers
- [ ] Run migration `002_views.sql` — `v_user_dashboard`, `v_city_buildings`
- [ ] Run migration `003_rls.sql` — Row Level Security policies
- [ ] Run migration `004_rpc_functions.sql` — `process_task_completion`, `recover_streak`, `purchase_shop_item`
- [ ] Run migration `005_cron_jobs.sql` — midnight streak check, grace reset, mayor rotation
- [ ] Set up Upstash Redis instance + connection from Edge Functions
- [ ] Set up Firebase Auth project + integrate with Flutter
- [ ] Populate `seed.sql` — task catalog (30+ tasks), shop items, achievement definitions
- [ ] Deploy Edge Function: `complete-task` (core loop — most critical)
- [ ] Deploy Edge Function: `get-leaderboard`
- [ ] Deploy Edge Function: `recover-streak`
- [ ] Deploy Edge Function: `purchase-item`
- [ ] Deploy Edge Function: `get-city-data`
- [ ] Deploy Edge Functions: `buy-streak-shield`, `join-neighborhood`, `found-neighborhood`

**Integration test:** Flutter app → Firebase Auth login → Supabase insert user → read back → verified.

---

#### Phase 2: Onboarding UI + Backend Integration (Week 2–3)

- [ ] **Splash screen** — Lottie animation, auth state check (`FirebaseAuth.instance.currentUser`), auto-redirect
- [ ] **Character Creation screen** — archetype selection cards (×4), name input with validation (3-20 chars), avatar config pickers
  - Backend: `PATCH /rest/v1/users` → write name, archetype, avatar_config
  - Backend: Assign `city_plot_x`, `city_plot_y` (next available plot in grid)
- [ ] **Task Picker screen** — category sections, toggleable task cards, frequency slider per task, live `HealthImpactService` calculation at bottom
  - Backend: `GET /rest/v1/task_catalog` → display all available tasks
  - Backend: `POST /rest/v1/user_tasks` + auto-create matching `streaks` row (DB trigger)
- [ ] `HealthImpactService` — load `health_impact_lookup.json`, compute Body Age/Lifespan/Disease Risk combo preview
- [ ] End-to-end flow: Splash → Character → Task Picker → Home (with data persisted to Supabase)

---

#### Phase 3: Core Loop UI + Backend (Week 3–5)

- [x] **Home Dashboard** — greeting (time-aware), level badge, today's task `ListView.builder`, health metrics 2×2 grid
  - Backend: `GET /rest/v1/v_user_dashboard?user_id=eq.{uid}` — single query returns tasks + streaks joined
  - Backend: Realtime subscription on `streaks` table → auto-update streak counts in UI
- [x] **Task Detail & Health Impact** — task header, health metric cards, earnings preview, "Start Workout" / "Mark Complete" CTAs
  - Backend: `complete-task` Edge Function call → receive { streakCount, statusEarned, coinsEarned, healthMessage }
- [x] **Health Connect integration** — `health` package → read step count, running, cycling for auto-verified tasks
- [x] **Workout Celebration** — confetti, Lottie trophy, animated count-up, health impact message
  - Backend: Display response data from `complete-task`
- [x] **Streak Recovery screen** — broken alert, grace days display, shield button, recovery cost table, 48hr countdown timer
  - Backend: `recover-streak` Edge Function (atomic coin deduction + streak restore)
  - Backend: `buy-streak-shield` Edge Function (deduct 150 coins + set `shield_active = TRUE`)
- [x] Status + Coins earning engine — formula: `10 × effective_difficulty × streak_multiplier × verification_weight`
- [ ] Verify midnight streak cron job works correctly (break streak → grace day consumed → broken state)

---

#### Phase 4: Social & Economy UI + Backend (Week 4–6)

- [ ] **Global Leaderboard** — segmented tabs (All/Month/Week), podium top 3, scrollable list
  - Backend: `get-leaderboard` Edge Function → Redis `ZREVRANGE` + profile hydration from Postgres
  - Tap user row → navigate to their profile
- [ ] **User Profile** — avatar + stats, achievements grid (earned=colored, locked=gray), neighborhood cards
  - Backend: `GET /rest/v1/users`, `GET /rest/v1/user_achievements`
  - Share Profile: screenshot → `share_plus`
- [ ] **Neighborhood Hub** — name/motto header, collective stats, rival comparison, raid boss progress bar, member list
  - Backend: `GET /rest/v1/neighborhoods`, `GET /rest/v1/neighborhood_members`, `GET /rest/v1/raid_bosses`
  - Realtime: subscription on `raid_bosses` table for live progress
  - Backend: `join-neighborhood`, `found-neighborhood` Edge Functions
- [ ] **Coin Shop** — tabs (Skins/Colors/Effects/Character), `GridView.builder` of items, purchase flow
  - Backend: `GET /rest/v1/shop_items`, `GET /rest/v1/user_inventory`
  - Backend: `purchase-item` Edge Function (atomic deduct + grant)
- [ ] **Push notifications** — Firebase Cloud Messaging setup, streak warning (6pm if not completed), weekly health summary
- [ ] **Achievement checking** — trigger checks after task completion (streak milestones, total completions, etc.)

**Milestone: All 11 Flutter screens complete and fully connected to Supabase backend. Core loop end-to-end working.**

---

### PART B: Unity 3D (Weeks 5–9)

#### Phase 5: 3D City World — Core Environment (Week 5–7) ⭐ Critical Path

- [ ] Unity project setup: URP, Cinemachine, PostProcessing, InputSystem, TextMeshPro, DOTween
- [ ] `CyberpunkSkybox.shader` — procedural sunset gradient + animated clouds + star field
- [ ] City grid ground plane — dark asphalt with subtle neon grid lines, road network from template
- [ ] `AtmosphericFog.shader` — distance-based purple-tinted fog
- [ ] `WaterSurface.shader` — planar reflection + wave normals + caustics (harbor area)
- [ ] URP Post-Processing Volume: Bloom, Color Grading (cyberpunk LUT), Vignette, Film Grain
- [ ] Baked lighting setup: directional sun/moon + ambient from skybox + emissive contributions
- [ ] `SkyboxController.cs` + `FogController.cs` + `WaterManager.cs` + `LightingManager.cs`

---

#### Phase 6: 3D Building Generation System (Week 6–8)

- [ ] Modular building prefabs: 4 categories × (base + 5 floor variants + 3 crown variants) = ~40 pieces
- [ ] `BuildingGenerator.cs` — read task data JSON → assemble Base + N × Floor + Crown
- [ ] `BuildingModules.cs` — category → architectural style mapping + random variation selection
- [ ] `BuildingWindow.shader` — emissive window grid with per-cell mask (lit based on streak recency)
- [ ] `WindowController.cs` — generate `_WindowMask` texture from `days_since_last_completion`
- [ ] `NeonGlow.shader` + `NeonSignManager.cs` — 3D TextMeshPro signs on facades, category-colored bloom
- [ ] `ConstructionCrane.cs` — crane prefab on buildings with active streak < 7 days
- [ ] `CrackedBuilding.shader` + `BuildingDecay.cs` — crack overlay + desaturation for broken streaks, dissolve heal animation for recovered
- [ ] `CityGrid.cs` — world grid layout, plot placement (200m × 200m per user), road generation between plots
- [ ] `DistrictLoader.cs` — load building data from JSON/REST, generate buildings for a user plot, signage (name + level)

---

#### Phase 7: Player & Cruise System (Week 7–9)

- [ ] Avatar model setup — hooded figure from Mixamo, walk/fly/idle animations
- [ ] `PlayerController.cs` — CharacterController (walking) / Rigidbody (flying), gravity toggle, movement input
- [ ] `CameraController.cs` — Cinemachine FreeLook rig: walking (close, slight tilt), flying (higher, wider FOV), bird's eye (top-down 45°)
- [ ] `AltitudeController.cs` — slider UI → smooth lerp between camera modes + movement mode toggle
- [ ] `CruiseMode.cs` — auto-forward at `cruiseSpeed`, toggle button, speed display (knots)
- [ ] `HUDController.cs` — altitude (FT), compass (N/S/E/W from camera Y rotation), speed, recording indicator
- [ ] `BuildingTooltip.cs` — raycast from screen tap → show glass popup (name, district, streak, height, "TAP TO SEE DETAILS")
- [ ] `HologramTooltip.shader` — semi-transparent scan-line glass material for tooltip popup
- [ ] `MinimapCamera.cs` — secondary camera overhead → RenderTexture → minimap UI image
- [ ] `CaptureManager.cs` — capture screenshot → save to file → send path to Flutter for sharing

---

#### Phase 8: Multi-User World (Week 8–9)

- [ ] `DistrictLoader.cs` — proximity trigger system: when player enters distance < 300m from unloaded plot, fetch data + generate
- [ ] Supabase REST calls from Unity: `GET /rest/v1/v_city_buildings?city_plot_x=...` via `UnityWebRequest`
- [ ] LOD system: full detail within 200m, simplified box silhouettes 200-500m, hidden beyond 500m
- [ ] District boundary glow ring + floating signage (TextMeshPro 3D: "Alex's District · Level 12")
- [ ] Plot unloading: destroy building GameObjects when player moves > 500m away (memory management)
- [ ] `DataModels.cs` — C# data classes matching Supabase view schema, JSON deserialization

---

### PART C: Flutter ↔ Unity Integration (Weeks 9–12)

#### Phase 9: Bridge Setup & Skyline Embedding (Week 9–10)

- [ ] Add `flutter_unity_widget` to Flutter project, configure iOS/Android build pipelines
- [ ] Export Unity project as Android library (`.aar`) + iOS framework
- [ ] `FlutterBridge.cs` (Unity side) — message listener: parse JSON from Flutter, dispatch to `CityManager`
- [ ] `UnityBridgeService` (Flutter side) — typed methods: `loadUserCity(uid)`, `onTaskCompleted(taskData)`, `switchToHelicopterMode()`, `captureScreenshot()`
- [ ] **Home Dashboard**: embed mini `UnityWidget` (200px height) showing user's own skyline silhouette
  - Flutter sends: `LoadUserCity` with current user's building data
  - Tap → navigate to full-screen skyline
- [ ] **Full skyline view**: full-screen `UnityWidget` with altitude slider, cruise button, HUD overlay
  - Flutter bottom nav bar visible at bottom (shared navigation)
  - "Exit to Skyline" → return to Flutter Home Dashboard
- [ ] Bridge bidirectional test: Flutter sends task data → Unity updates building → Unity sends "building tapped" → Flutter shows detail

---

#### Phase 10: Deep Integration Features (Week 10–11)

- [ ] **Workout Celebration → Building Growth**: after `complete-task` Edge Function succeeds:
  - Flutter sends `OnTaskCompleted` to Unity with { taskId, newStreakCount, category }
  - Unity plays building-grow animation (DOTween scale Y) + construction crane removal (if streak ≥ 7)
  - Mini Unity view in celebration screen shows the specific building's before/after
- [ ] **Leaderboard → Visit Skyline**: tap a user row in Leaderboard:
  - Flutter sends `LoadUserCity(theirUid)` to Unity
  - Unity loads their plot data from Supabase REST → generates their buildings
  - Camera flies to their district
- [ ] **Neighborhood Hub → Collective Skyline**: mini Unity embed showing merged neighborhood buildings
  - Flutter sends `LoadNeighborhoodCity(neighborhoodId)` → Unity loads all member plots
- [ ] **Coin Shop → Skin Preview**: tap a building skin item:
  - Flutter sends `PreviewSkin(taskId, skinId)` to Unity
  - Unity applies the skin material → user sees live 3D preview
  - On purchase confirmation → Flutter calls `purchase-item` Edge Function → sends `ApplySkin` to Unity
- [ ] **Profile → Skyline Preview**: mini Unity embed of own skyline (same as home dashboard embed)
- [ ] **Streak Recovery → Building Heal**: on successful recovery:
  - Flutter sends `OnStreakRecovered(taskId)` to Unity
  - Unity plays crack-dissolve heal animation on the building

---

#### Phase 11: Polish, Performance & Launch (Week 11–12)

- [ ] **Performance tuning:**
  - Unity: LOD distance tuning, draw call budget < 100, texture compression (ASTC), occlusion culling
  - Flutter: widget rebuild optimization, `const` constructors, image caching
  - Memory: plot unloading when distant, texture streaming
- [ ] **Sound design:**
  - Ambient city hum + distant traffic
  - Cruise mode: wind sound, engine hum scaled by speed
  - Building grow: deep bass + glass chime SFX
  - UI: subtle click/tap sounds, streak break alert
- [ ] **Haptic feedback**: task completion, building tap, cruise mode toggle, purchase confirmation
- [ ] **APK size optimization**: target < 80MB
  - Addressables for 3D assets (load on demand)
  - Strip unused Unity shaders
  - Compress audio to OGG
- [ ] **Edge case testing:**
  - Streak midnight rollover across timezones
  - No internet → offline mode (cached data, queue completions)
  - Multiple rapid task completions
  - Building state after streak break → recovery → re-completion
- [ ] **Firebase Crashlytics + Analytics setup**
- [ ] **End-to-end test**: New user → onboarding → pick tasks → complete workout → see building grow → cruise city → visit neighbor → break streak → recover → buy skin
- [ ] **Beta testing (20-30 users)** — TestFlight / Firebase App Distribution

---

## 9. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| `flutter_unity_widget` stability | High | Test bridge in Phase 9 (week 9-10); fallback to native UAAL |
| 3D performance on low-end devices | High | LOD system, draw call budget < 100, ASTC textures, occlusion culling |
| Multi-user data loading latency | Medium | Proximity lazy-loading, silhouette placeholders, Supabase pagination |
| Unity APK size bloat | Medium | Addressables, strip shaders, compress textures |
| Streak midnight timezone issues | High | All streak logic in pg_cron using UTC timestamps |
| Supabase Edge Function cold starts | Low | Critical paths (completion) called frequently enough to stay warm |
| Building tooltip raycast accuracy | Medium | Enlarged box colliders, visual hover highlight |

---

## 10. Verification Plan

### Automated
- **Flutter**: Widget tests for all 11 screens, unit tests for `HealthImpactService`, `StreakService`, status calculator
- **Backend**: Integration tests against Supabase local dev (supabase start) — full task completion flow → streak update → leaderboard update
- **Unity**: Play mode tests for `BuildingGenerator` (height, category, module count)
- **Redis**: Verify leaderboard ZADD/ZREVRANGE round-trip with test data

### Manual
1. **Skyline accuracy**: Test user with known data → verify building heights/colors match expected
2. **Cruise controls**: Physical device — joystick, altitude slider, cruise mode feel smooth (30fps+)
3. **Multi-user**: 5 test accounts → all plots visible when cruising
4. **Streak flow**: Break → grace day → break again → recovery → 48hr expiry
5. **Bridge**: Task completion in Flutter → building grows in Unity → screenshot → shared via Flutter
6. **Performance**: Profile on Pixel 4a baseline — target 30fps+ in city, 60fps in Flutter UI
